<p>of defence &amp; handling of his artillery &amp; machine guns is too good. However, enough of war!</p>
<p>We are just on the point of being relieved &amp; going into billets at the rear for a spell. We shall be out a few weeks and &ndash; (I say it with hushed breath) I may find myself crossing the old channel for a few days. I have written to Sis &amp; told her that I may get a chance of a trip, so hope I wont be stopped.</p>
<p>This billeting arrangement is a most excellent idea. All the men have comfortable weather proof  quarters, and baths etc abound in plenty. I was quite surprised to find that the weather could be so hot in these parts. The last few days have be most oppressive.</p>
<p>Have not seen any of the old hands lately as we are detached from our Infantry at present. Saw Maurice Lenehan a week</p>
